'''Brewing''' is part of the [[Cooking]] skill that allows players to create [[alcohol]]ic [[drinks]], specifically [[ale]]s and [[cider]] by fermenting ingredients. They all provide [[temporary skill boost]]s for varying [[skill]]s as well as lowering some combination of [[Attack]], [[Strength]], and [[Defence]]. Every ale and cider has a [[Mature ale|mature]] form which increases both the negative and positive boosts.

There are only two places where brewing can be done, [[fermenting vat]]s, one in eastern [[Keldagrim]] on the {{FloorNumber|uk=1}} of the [[Laughing Miner Pub]] and the other in [[Port Phasmatys]] underneath the [[The Green Ghost]] pub.

==Brewing Process==
===Ales===
The main ingredients for ales are: 2 [[bucket of water]], 2 [[barley malt]], 1 [[ale yeast]], and optionally: 1 [[the stuff]]
{{Instructions
|step1 = Use 2 [[bucket of water]] on the [[fermenting vat]]
|step2 = Use 2 [[barley malt]] on the fermenting vat
|step3 = ''Optional:'' Use 1 [[the stuff]] on the fermenting vat, increasing the chance to mature the ale from 5% to 36%{{Refn|Testing has shown it is not 64% as Mod Ash was previously cited and likely closer to 36%. Please comment on [[Talk:Brewing]] with questions, comments, or if you want to contribute data.}}
|step4 = Use the ingredients specific to the brew type you want to make
|step5 = Use 1 [[ale yeast]] on the fermenting vat
|step6 = Wait for 3 x 640 minute cycles (with [[the stuff]] added, between 3 x 640 and 16 x 640 minutes)
|step7 = Use the valve to drain the completed ale into the barrel
|step8 = Use 8 [[beer glass]]es or 2 [[calquat keg]]s on the barrel full of the completed ale
}}

===Cider===
The main ingredients for cider are: 4 buckets of [[apple mush]], 1 [[ale yeast]]
{{Instructions
|step1 = Use 4 buckets of [[apple mush]] on the [[fermenting vat]]
|step2 = Use 1 [[ale yeast]] on the fermenting vat
|step3 = Wait for 3 x 640 minute cycles
|step6 = Use the valve to drain the completed ale into the barrel
|step7 = Use 8 [[beer glass]]es or 2 [[calquat keg]]s on the barrel full of the completed cider
}}

===Ingredient notes===
* [[Barley malt]] can be made by using [[barley]] on a [[range]].
* [[Ale yeast]] can be purchased from [[Blandebir]] for {{NoCoins|25}} coins or [[Metarialus]] for 5 [[ectotoken]]s. You must have an empty pot in your inventory for them to give you ale yeast.
* [[The stuff]] can only be purchased from [[Honest Jimmy]] with 50 [[pieces of eight]] from playing the [[Trouble Brewing]] [[minigame]].
* [[Apple mush]] is made with an [[apple press]], there is one next to each fermenting vat. Four [[cooking apple]]s and a [[bucket]] are required.

==Fermentation==
Brewing relies on the same farming cycles as hardwood trees, redwood trees, and anima.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1001900008910868481|date=30 March 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/uRPX1|archivedate=14 August 2020|quote=Yes, for any patch that used the farming timer - which I think is every patch except My Arm's one where he grows the goutweed during the quest since that becomes grown only when you kill the bird. It affects brewing too.}} There are three stages that each brew must go through in order to complete, advancing to the next stage at the next '''growth tick'''.{{CiteNews|author=The Old School Team|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/farming-timer-rework--skilling-qol|title=Farming Timer Rework & Skilling QoL|notes=A growth tick is similar to clocks that tick every 5, 10, 20, 40 minutes and so on. This is expanded upon in [[Farming#Mechanics|Farming Mechanics]]|newsdate=15 February 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/SPmUw|archivedate=28 May 2020}} Brewing ticks '''only''' occur every 640 minutes. However, there is an offset for farming ticks that is '''different for each player''' and persists through logins.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1112039756764983296|date=30 March 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/RzheL|archivedate=28 May 2020|quote=It persists through logins, and does not re-randomise.}} To determine this offset, note the time when a hardwood, redwood, or anima patch grows one stage, or when a brew completes and compare with the closest time on the table below. Apply the time difference to every time in the table. For example, if a brew completes at 10:18 AM on Day 1, subtract 22 minutes from each time listed.

{|class="wikitable"
!Cycle length!!Main crops!!Base growth times(GMT)
|-
|640 minutes
|Hardwood, Redwood, Anima, Brews
|Day 1: 12:00 AM, 10:40 AM, 9:20 PM<br/>Day 2: 8:00 AM, 6:40 PM<br/>Day 3: 5:20 AM, 4:00 PM<br/>Day 4: 2:40 AM, 1:20 PM
|}
In the table above, {{#time: l j F Y}} is Day {{#expr:floor({{#time:U}} / 86400) mod 4 + 1}}. (Note: This is usually today, but does not always update immediately when the date changes. Refresh the page to force it to update.)

The first stage begins immediately after adding [[ale yeast]]. The second stage will occur on the next growth tick where it is possible for the still fermenting brew to become mature. The final stage has three possible outcomes: a completed normal [[ale]], a [[mature ale]], or a bad ale. Bad ales are green and useless, it must be drained from the vat then from the barrel. There is roughly a 20% chance for an ale to go bad.{{Fact}}

Standard times to complete when not using [[the stuff]], is at minimum 1,281 minutes, about 21 hours and 20 minutes, or 1 minute past 3 growth ticks. At maximum is 1,920 minutes or 32 hours which is the full 3 growth cycles. This depends on when you start the fermentation process during the current cycle. 

===Mature brews===
With normal brewing, a player can randomly make a full vat of matured ale, however a majority of the time it will complete as a non-matured ale. The chances of ale maturing naturally is 5%, but adding [[the stuff]] increases this chance to 36%.{{Refn|Testing has shown it is not 64% as Mod Ash was previously cited and likely closer to 36%. Please comment on [[Talk:Brewing]] with questions, comments, or if you want to contribute data.}} Cider is the only brew that the stuff is '''not''' used for, it must always become mature naturally. Mature ales provide stronger boosts, heal more, and provide larger deboosts. The stuff is purchasable from [[Honest Jimmy]] for 50 [[pieces of eight]], a reward from the [[Trouble Brewing]] [[minigame]]. If attempting to make mature ales, it is highly recommended using the stuff. It must be added right after the [[barley malt]] is added, it is '''not''' possible to put it in afterwards.

Note: "The Stuff" is '''not''' required to make a mature ale, it simply increases the chances that it does mature.

Standard times to complete when not using the stuff, is at minimum 1,281 minutes, about 21 hours and 20 minutes, or 1 minute past 3 growth ticks. At maximum is 10,240 minutes or 1 week. This will depend on when you start the fermentation process during the current cycle.

